<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="tight-adj">tight <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /taɪt/    美 /taɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>紧的；绷紧的 ：</strong></h4>
<p>反 loose  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The drawer is so tight that I can’t open it. 
抽屉太紧，我打不开。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is wearing a tight pair of jeans. 
她穿着一条紧身牛仔裤。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>(时间、空间) 紧凑的；(经济) 紧张的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I can’t see you next week because the <strong>schedule</strong> is very <strong>tight</strong>. 
我下周日程排得满满的，所以不能见你。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There was a tight group of people around the speaker. 
演讲者周围严严实实地挤了一群人。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Money was</strong> always <strong>tight</strong>, but we had a roof over our heads, food on the table, clothes on our backs. 
虽然总是缺钱，但我们有房住，有饭吃，有衣穿。</p><footer>2008 浙江</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>困难的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He’s a good man to have around if you’re ever in a tight corner. 
如果你有困难，有他在身旁会很有用的。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>严格的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The airport security is very tight. 
机场的安保工作很严格。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>My schedule is very <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (紧凑的) right now, but I’ll try to fit you in.
  （2011 浙江改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. tight  </p></div>